The paper discusses the use of data-driven models in Intelligent Transportation Systems (ITS), which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). It also discusses the engineering requirements and challenges of implementing these models in real-world systems (cs.CE), as well as the need for security and reliability in ITS (cs.CR). Finally, the paper touches on the use of control systems and the need for adaptability in ITS models (cs.SY).
